5_12	0.09090909090909091	Somewhere between 15-20 percent may outgrow it, but 65-75 percent continue to have symptoms that impair them markedly as adults''.
5_13	0.5	ADHD is a neurological and genetic disorder that, Barkley said, is the most widely inherited trait of any psychiatric disorder.
5_14	0.0	Estimates are that 2 million to 5 million adults have ADHD.
5_15	0.14285714285714285	It is almost impossible to acquire the syndrome in adulthood, except through trauma to the head.
5_16	0.0	Most cases of adult diagnosis occur in those whose childhood disorder was not identified.
