6_43	0.0	In one of the largest studies of its kind ever conducted, a team of researchers at six sites around the country, led by Jensen, followed 579 children with ADHD for 14 months to assess their progress with various forms of treatment.
6_44	0.2	The researchers found that medication was substantially more effective than behavior-modification therapy in treating children with ADHD alone.
6_45	0.0	In cases where children had problems in addition to ADHD, such as depression or anxiety, combining medication with behavior therapy provided an advantage.
