10_40	0.0	''I knew I was intelligent, yet it didn't correspond to anything.
10_41	0.0	I knew the material but I couldn't make it translate into anything like good grades''.
10_42	0.0	Lippman's parents were well-off enough to send him to a private high school near their home in Tenafly, N.J., where he received plenty of one-on-one attention.
10_43	0.22727272727272727	On the strength of a personal interview and an award-winning senior year project on Attention Deficit Disorder (the success he says started his momentum), he was accepted to Union College, a highly selective private college in Schenectady.
