13_6	0.14285714285714285	Stimulant-based medication long has been the primary treatment for the disorder, and methylphenidate has accounted for 80 percent of the prescriptions written during the past decade.
13_7	0.16666666666666666	Adderall, a mixture of two types of amphetamines, initially was developed as a weight loss drug in the 1960s and later fell out of use.
13_8	0.4	The manufacturer revived it several years ago after tests showed it was effective in treating ADHD.
13_9	0.6666666666666666	It has been used largely for children who don't respond to methylphenidate.
13_10	0.0	Pliszka's study is part of an effort by doctors to compare the two drugs in controlled tests.
13_11	0.0	``It shows that we can use Adderall first,'' Pliszka said.
13_12	0.0	``Physicians and families should feel very comfortable about using it.
13_13	0.0	That's the main finding of this study''.
13_14	0.0	The study involved 58 children who got Adderall, methylphenidate or a placebo _ a harmless, unmedicated preparation _ for three weeks.
13_15	0.0	During that time, the children were evaluated periodically by teachers and parents, using a scale that assessed whether their behavior and attention problems were improving.
13_16	0.0	Pliszka said the research showed both medications were superior to the placebo and that Adderall performed better than methylphenidate.
